[Swagger Codegen Maven plugin](https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-codegen/tree/master/modules/swagger-codegen-maven-plugin) can bundle a multi-file OpenAPI definition into a single file. Use plugin version 2.x for OpenAPI 2.0, and version [3.x](https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-codegen/tree/3.0.0/modules/swagger-codegen-maven-plugin) for OpenAPI 3.0. Note that the 2.x and 3.x versions have different `groupId`s and slightly different config values.

Example for OpenAPI 2.0:
```
&lt;plugin&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;io.swagger&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;swagger-codegen-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;2.4.26&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;executions&gt;
        &lt;execution&gt;
            &lt;goals&gt;
                &lt;goal&gt;generate&lt;/goal&gt;
            &lt;/goals&gt;
            &lt;configuration&gt;
                &lt;inputSpec&gt;${project.basedir}/src/main/resources/openapi.yaml&lt;/inputSpec&gt;

                &lt;!-- Use &#39;swagger-yaml&#39; to get resolved YAML or &#39;swagger&#39; to get resolved JSON --&gt;
                &lt;language&gt;swagger-yaml&lt;/language&gt;

                &lt;configOptions&gt;
					&lt;!-- Default file name is swagger.yaml or swagger.json --&gt;
					&lt;outputFile&gt;openapi.yaml&lt;/outputFile&gt;
                &lt;/configOptions&gt;
            &lt;/configuration&gt;
        &lt;/execution&gt;
    &lt;/executions&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
```

Example for OpenAPI 3.0:

```xml
&lt;plugin&gt;
	&lt;groupId&gt;io.swagger.codegen.v3&lt;/groupId&gt;
	&lt;artifactId&gt;swagger-codegen-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
	&lt;version&gt;3.0.33&lt;/version&gt;
	&lt;executions&gt;
		&lt;execution&gt;
			&lt;goals&gt;
				&lt;goal&gt;generate&lt;/goal&gt;
			&lt;/goals&gt;
			&lt;configuration&gt;
				&lt;inputSpec&gt;${project.basedir}/src/main/resources/openapi.yaml&lt;/inputSpec&gt;

				&lt;!-- Use &#39;openapi-yaml&#39; to get resolved YAML or &#39;openapi&#39; to get resolved JSON --&gt;
				&lt;language&gt;openapi-yaml&lt;/language&gt;

				&lt;!-- Default is ${project.build.directory}/generated-sources/swagger --&gt;
				&lt;output&gt;_build&lt;/output&gt;

				&lt;configOptions&gt;
					&lt;!-- Default file name is openapi.yaml or openapi.json --&gt;
					&lt;outputFile&gt;openapi.yaml&lt;/outputFile&gt;
				&lt;/configOptions&gt;
			&lt;/configuration&gt;
		&lt;/execution&gt;
	&lt;/executions&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
```
